<div class=shim12pt>&nbsp;</div><div id=AdditionalPhotos style='text-align: center; width: 100%;'><div style='all:initial;margin-left:0px;'><div class=photoafter><div style='max-width:420px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;'><a target=_blank href='PhotoFullSize.asp?PhotoID=751620'><img loading=lazy class=photoimage src=Photos7/751/Photo751620.jpg?924202311700AM style='max-height:300px;' alt='Charles R. Jonas Federal Building image. Click for full size.' title='Charles R. Jonas Federal Building. Click for full size.'></a><div class=imagecredit style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>Photographed By J.T. Lambrou,  September 1, 2023</div> <!-- imagecredit --> <div class=imagecaption style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>4. Charles R. Jonas Federal Building</div><div class=imagesubcaption  style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>This is the federal building discussed on the marker which sits on the land formerly occupied by the Charlotte Mint.</div></div></div></div><div style='all:initial;margin-left:0px;'><div class=photoafter><div style='max-width:419px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;'><a target=_blank href='PhotoFullSize.asp?PhotoID=751622'><img loading=lazy class=photoimage src=Photos7/751/Photo751622.jpg?924202313700AM style='max-height:248px;' alt='Mint Building image. Click for full size.' title='Mint Building. Click for full size.'></a><div class=imagecredit style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>Photographed By J.T. Lambrou,  August 30, 2023</div> <!-- imagecredit --> <div class=imagecaption style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>5. Mint Building</div><div class=imagesubcaption  style='padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px;'>The Mint Building was relocated to this location in 1936 and became the Mint Museum, a gallery for art.</div></div></div></div></div><div class=shim6pt>&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;<br><span class=sectionhead>Credits. </span><a name=WantList></a>This page was last revised on  September 